simplified to - 1.

00:06:01.410 --> 00:06:04.410
In the limit.

00:06:04.410 --> 00:06:08.100
So now, I've got a negative
number divided by a tiny

00:06:08.100 --> 00:06:10.100
positive number.

00:06:10.100 --> 00:06:11.940
And so, somebody want to
tell me what that is?

00:06:11.940 --> 00:06:16.750
Negative infinity.

00:06:16.750 --> 00:06:21.460
So, we just evaluated this
function from one side.

00:06:21.460 --> 00:06:29.190
And if you follow through the
other side, so this one here,

00:06:29.190 --> 00:06:31.140
you get something very similar,
except that this

00:06:31.140 --> 00:06:34.120
should be -- whoops, what
