00:06:34.120 --> 00:06:37.690
I meant this.

00:06:37.690 --> 00:06:40.810
I want it -2 the same base
point, but I want

00:06:40.810 --> 00:06:43.750
to go from the left.

00:06:43.750 --> 00:06:47.780
So that's going to be -
2 + 1, same numerator.

00:06:47.780 --> 00:06:52.540
And then this - 2 on the left +
2, and that's going to come

00:06:52.540 --> 00:07:00.670
out to be - 1 / 0 -, which
is plus infinity.

00:07:00.670 --> 00:07:02.348
Or just plain infinity,
we don't have to

00:07:02.348 --> 00:07:10.520
put the plus sign.

00:07:10.520 --> 00:07:13.090
So this is the first part
of the problem.

00:07:13.090 --> 00:07:16.630
And the second piece, to get
ourselves started, you could

00:07:16.630 --> 00:07:18.260
evaluate this function
at any point.

00:07:18.260 --> 00:07:21.340
This is just the most
interesting point, alright?

00:07:21.340 --> 00:07:22.550
This is just the most
interesting

00:07:22.550 --> 00:07:25.270
place to evaluate it.

00:07:25.270 --> 00:07:28.130
Now, the next thing that I'd
like to do is to pay attention

00:07:28.130 --> 00:07:32.130
