00:12:35.950 --> 00:12:39.600
So this makes it easy to see
what the derivative is.

00:12:39.600 --> 00:12:42.730
Because the derivative of
a constant is 0, right?

00:12:42.730 --> 00:12:46.640
So this is, derivative,
is just going to

00:12:46.640 --> 00:12:49.300
be, switch the sign.

00:12:49.300 --> 00:12:53.410
This is what I wrote before.

00:12:53.410 --> 00:12:55.230
And that explains it.

00:12:55.230 --> 00:12:57.940
But incidentally, it
also shows you that

00:12:57.940 --> 00:13:04.890
that this is a hyperbola.

00:13:04.890 --> 00:13:09.620
These are just two curves
of a hyperbola.

00:13:09.620 --> 00:13:12.240
So now, let's check the sign.

00:13:12.240 --> 00:13:15.290
It's already totally obvious
to us that this is just a

00:13:15.290 --> 00:13:15.940
double check.

00:13:15.940 --> 00:13:18.710
We didn't actually even have to
pay any attention to this.

00:13:18.710 --> 00:13:19.790
It had better be true.

00:13:19.790 --> 00:13:22.220
This is just going to check
our arithmetic.

00:13:22.220 --> 00:13:24.570
Namely, it's increasing here.

00:13:24.570 --> 00:13:26.610
It's increasing there.

00:13:26.610 --> 00:13:27.830
That's got to be true.

00:13:27.830 --> 00:13:31.620
And, sure enough, this is
positive, as you can see it's

00:13:31.620 --> 00:13:32.930
1 over a square.

00:13:32.930 --> 00:13:34.070
So it is increasing.

00:13:34.070 --> 00:13:35.630
So we checked it.

00:13:35.630 --> 00:13:39.370
But now, there's one more thing
that I want to just have

00:13:39.370 --> 00:13:40.720
you watch out about.

00:13:40.720 --> 00:13:46.980
So this means that
f is increasing.

00:13:46.980 --> 00:13:51.830
On the interval minus infinity
&lt; x &lt; - 2.

00:13:51.830 --> 00:13:56.700
And also from - 2 all the
